summary: I don’t and probably never will understand the hate towards Brie Larson. I’ve been a huge fan of her work since Room ( I think...
body: I don’t and probably never will understand the hate towards Brie Larson. I’ve been a huge fan of her work since Room ( I think she totally deserves the Oscar ) but I never followed her on social media or watched interviews. I started to do it right after the release of Captain Marvel and she seems to be really sweet and caring. However, the hate I saw on YouTube comments and twitter… it’s truly scary… You don’t like a character, fine. You don’t like the actress, fine. But the disrespect and hate is going way too far!

Peter: *running out of the room*

Ned: Where are you going? It was just a jo-

summary: Accidentally got into an argument about whether captain marvel was a lesbian or not. I kept asking for evidence, and the best I...
body:
Accidentally got into an argument about whether captain marvel was a lesbian or not. I kept asking for evidence, and the best I got was that Larson wants lgbt characters in the mcu and Larson saying carol and that other lady are the love story because they remind Larson of her own girlfriends. So to me, her sexuality is still up in the air.

I’m not against the idea, I just want to be sure the character I call [sexuality] is actually that sexuality. Idk why, just a little pet peeve of mine

summary: Carol was fucking wasted in Endgame. I won't say any more (no death, at least, I will say that, she does not die, Carol Danvers...
body:
Carol was fucking wasted in Endgame. I won’t say any more (no death, at least, I will say that, she does not die, Carol Danvers is safe) but if you haven’t seen it yet, just know she shows up for like 7 minutes out of a 3 hour film and is completely boring w/no flair or charisma.

Carol stans, I’m so so sorry the Russos did this to you my loves. You deserve far better.
